Siddhant Darpan
Mahamahopaddyaya Chandrasekhar Sinha Samanta (1835-1904), better known as Pathani Samanta to all Odias, was an accomplished naked-eye astronomer. He was one of the few ‘Siddhantic’ astronomers who had worked many centuries later than the recognised Siddhantic period. He lived and carried out his astronomical work at a time when advanced instruments were in use elsewhere. Yet the accuracy of Samanta’s data collected with homemade instruments still amazes those who study his work.
His painstaking observations and interpretations are chronicled in his magnum opus ‘Siddhant Darpan’. Presented here are the digital copies of his original Sanskrit text and Odia, Hindi and English translations along with mathematical interpretations of and discussions on his work.
